# Handoff — <topic / phase>

A distinct document (standards/09 §3): it carries **current state + next action**, not the
*why* (ADR), the *what* (feature spec), or the *how* (implementation plan). A phase report
doubles as a handoff **only if** it includes everything below.

## Current state
<what is done and live right now; the relevant plan/spec + revision>

## Environment
<where it runs / branches / deploy revision / how to start it>

## Evidence
<CI / tests / runtime proof of the current state — links, git-verifiable>

## Blockers / open issues
<what's stuck, what's undecided, anything risky in flight>

## Next action
<the single most important next step — concrete enough to start cold>
